All -X flags are either SVOPs with a GV attached,
or UNOPs with a value starting in $op->first.

-r fteread
-w ftewrite
-x fteexec
-o fteowned

-R ftrread
-W ftrwrite
-X ftrexec
-O ftrowned

-e ftis
-z ftzero
-s ftsize

-f ftfile
-d ftdir
-l ftlink
-p ftpipe
-S ftsock
-b ftblk
-c ftchr
-t fttty

-u ftsuid
-g ftsgid
-k ftsvtx

-T fttext
-B ftbinary

-M ftmtime
-A ftatime
-C ftctime
